note: This flare occurred with a filament eruption on the west limb. No numbered active region is or was located where this filament ejection is centered.

Partially occulted flare from former Active Region 14153 located just beyond the southwest limb of the Earth-facing disk as seen in GOES SUVI 131 and corroborated by brightening seen in STEREO A EUVI 195.
Additional contribution seen as brightening in SDO AIA 131 from AR 14173 (S17W60).
Brightening from a simultaneous eruption from AR 14173 (S18W83), best seen in seen in SDO AIA 131, may have contributed to the total intensity of this flare.
No current active region designation to flaring area, located just inside the SE limb and distinctly separate from nearby AR 14188 (S09E70 at flare peak).

This flare originated from a region beyond the southeast limb which has since been numbered as Active Region 14197. There may have been additional, but minor, flaring contribution from Active Region 14191 (N12E61) at the time of this event.
Flare on (or from just behind) the NE limb.
Associated with brightening from post-eruptive arcades seen in SDO AIA 131.
